org.openwms.core.module

Class Module

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ameba.integration.jpa.BaseEntity
      • org.openwms.core.module.Module
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, org.ameba.integration.TypedEntity<Long>

    @Entity
public class Module
extends org.ameba.integration.jpa.BaseEntity
implements Serializable
    A Module represents an Adobe Flex Module and is used to store some basic information about that module, i.e. a name, an URL where the module from, or whether the Adobe Flex Module should be loaded on application startup.
    Author:
    Heiko Scherrer
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Field Detail

      • moduleName

        private String moduleName
        Unique name of the Module (natural key, unique, not-null).

      • url

        private String url
        URL from where to load this Module (unique, not-null).

      • loaded

        private boolean loaded
        Flag used on the client side to store whether the Module is actually loaded or not. It's a dynamic value and not persisted.

      • loadOnStartup

        private boolean loadOnStartup
        true when the Module should be loaded on application startup.

      • startupOrder

        private int startupOrder
        Defines the startup order compared with other Modules. Modules with a lower startupOrder are loaded before this one.

      • description

        private String description
        A description text of this Module.

      • NQ_FIND_ALL

        public static final String NQ_FIND_ALL
        Query to find all Modules. Name is "Module.findAll" .

        Constant Field Values

      • NQ_FIND_BY_UNIQUE_QUERY

        public static final String NQ_FIND_BY_UNIQUE_QUERY
        Query to find one Module by its natural key.
      • Query parameter index 1 : The moduleName of the Module to search for

        • Name is "Module.findByModuleName" .
